Due to further blasting taking place off the N2, both the north and south bounds carriageways will be temporary closed for safety reasons on Tuesday, June 22, from 12.30 pm to 1 pm. The N2 will be closed between Queen Nandi Drive, on the northbound, and at Gateway interchange. This will also include the on and off ramps to KwaMashu. Motorists are urged to stay away from the N2 between the times mentioned and to expect congestion and delays on all arterial roads.